#libraries
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import random
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, ExtraTreesClassifier, AdaBoostClassifier
from xgboost import XGBClassifier

#custom
import utils
import plots
import transformers as tran

LABEL = "1Y_default"
SEED = 42

%matplotlib inline  
%load_ext autoreload
%autoreload 2

random.seed(SEED)
In [2]:
#read from csvs
train_df = pd.read_csv("train_selected.csv", na_filter = False)
test_df = pd.read_csv("test_selected.csv", na_filter = False)
In [3]:
#numerically encoded categoricals
to_categorical = ["Country", "HomeOwnershipType", "MaritalStatus", "OccupationArea", "UseOfLoan", 
                  "MonthlyPayment", "NewCreditCustomer", "Gender", "VerificationType", "Education"]
for feature in to_categorical:
    train_df[feature] = train_df[feature].astype("category")
    test_df[feature] = test_df[feature].astype("category")

In [5]:
#model definitions
models = {
        "LogisticRegression" : LogisticRegression(penalty="l2",C=1e42, random_state=SEED), #huge ivnverse penalty (sklearn does not provide non-regularized logit)
        "DecisionTree" : DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=SEED),
        "DecisionTree_3" : DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=3, random_state=SEED),
        "DecisionTree_7" : DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=7, random_state=SEED),
        "RandomForest" : RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=SEED),
        "ExtraTrees" : ExtraTreesClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=SEED),
        "AdaBoost" : AdaBoostClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=SEED),
        "XGBoost" : XGBClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=SEED)
        }
#transformer definition    
transformer = tran.OHE_transformer()

results = {}

for model in models.keys():
    results[model] = utils.experiment(models[model], transformer, train_df, test_df, LABEL, figsize=(11, 20))

results_df = pd.DataFrame.from_dict(results, orient="index")
fitted_models = results_df.pop("model")
results_df = results_df.reindex(columns=["roc_test", "roc_train", "gini_test", "gini_train", "fit_time"])
results_df.sort_values("roc_test", ascending=False, inplace=True)
